'''Diderik Børsting Schnitler''' (born 23 October 1946) is a Norwegian businessperson.

He hails from [[Stabekk]], and in his younger days he was the treasurer and an active [[tennis]] player for Stabekk TK.<ref name=stabak>{{cite news|url=http://www.stabak.no/klubben/article1605.ece|title=Diderik Schnitler ny styreformann i Stabæk Holding|last=Mæhlum|first=Lars Jarle|date=1 July 2009|publisher=Stabæk Fotball|language=Norwegian|accessdate=7 July 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927061454/http://www.stabak.no/klubben/article1605.ece|archivedate=27 September 2011|df=}}</ref> He graduated from the [[Norwegian Institute of Technology]] with a Bachelor of Science degree in 1970. He was hired as an engineer in [[Jarlsø Støperi]] in 1974, and was chief executive from 1976 to 1983. He was the chief executive officer of [[Kaldnes Mekaniske Verksted|Kaldnes]] from 1983 to 1986 and [[EB Anker Sønnak]] from 1986 to 1989.<ref name=ww>{{cite web|url=http://www.wilhelmsen.com/about/invest/corporate/BoardOfDirectors/Pages/DiderikSchnitler.aspx|title=Schnitler, Diderik|publisher=Wilh. Wilhelmsen|accessdate=7 July 2011}}</ref> In the 1980s he was a board member of [[Larvik Jernstøperi]], [[Vestfold Jernlager]], [[EB Consultants]] and Scanmar and chair of [[Sandefjord Airport]].<ref name=dn89>{{cite news|title=Schnitler overtar etter Karl Glad|last=Fardal|first=Signy|authorlink=Signy Fardal|work=Dagens Næringsliv|page=32|date=14 April 1989|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He was elected leader of the [[Federation of Norwegian Manufacturing Industries]] in 1989.<ref name=dn89/> He left that position already in October 1989.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tegnander ny TBL-formann|last=|first=|work=Aftenposten|page=16|date=31 October 1989|language=Norwegian}}</ref> After the [[Norwegian parliamentary election, 1989]], [[Syse's Cabinet]] assumed office, and Schnitler was appointed [[State Secretary (Norway)|State Secretary]] in the [[Norwegian Ministry of Industry|Ministry of Industry]]. He belonged to the [[Høyre|Conservative Party]]. He lost that job in 1990 when Syse's Cabinet fell,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.regjeringen.no/en/The-Government/previous-governments/the-structure-of-the-registry/governments/modern-times/governments-since-1945/jan-p-syses-government-1989---1990.html?id=438730|title=Jan P. Syse's Government|publisher=[[Government.no]]|accessdate=4 February 2009}}</ref> but immediately became president of Kværner Shipbuilding and vice president of the [[Kværner|Kværner Group]].<ref name=ww/> He also served as president of the [[Confederation of Norwegian Enterprise]] from 1994 to 1996.<ref>{{cite news|title=Schnitler vant NHO-kampen|last=Hellestøl|first=Yngve|work=Aftenposten|page=30|date=24 November 1994|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Onarheim til topps i NHO|last=Moy|first=Ragnhild|work=Aftenposten|page=25|date=29 November 1996|language=Norwegian}}</ref> From 1998 to 2000 he was the CEO of [[Saga Petroleum]]; he stepped down to become a professional board member.<ref name=ww/> His period with Saga was disastrous for the company, after a series of unfavorable financial dispositions, and the company ceased to exist and was acquired by Norsk Hydro.<ref>{{cite news|title=Alt har gått galt for Schnitler |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/nyheter/1999/06/12/167687.html |first=Torgeir |last=Lorentzen| date=12 June 1999|newspaper=[[Dagbladet]]|accessdate=2 January 2014}}</ref>

Since 2002 he has chaired the board of the global shipping company [[Wilh. Wilhelmsen]].<ref name=ww/> In 2009 he became chair of [[Stabæk Holding]].<ref name=stabak/>

He is a fellow of the [[Norwegian Academy of Technological Sciences]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ntva.no/index.php?option=com_club&view=member&id=391%3Aschnitler-diderik-borsting&Itemid=60|title=Medlemmer: SCHNITLER, Diderik Børsting|publisher=[[Norwegian Academy of Technological Sciences]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=29 December 2013}}</ref>

