'''EnPowered''' is a Canadian [[energy management]] organization, established in 2015. The company groups together consumers and businesses to get a lower [[Group buying|group-buying]] rate for energy and control their energy usage as well as costs.

It was founded by Tomas Van Stee in 2015 in [[Toronto]],<ref>{{cite web|title=EnPowered Launches into Energy Saving - StartUp HERE Toronto|url=http://startupheretoronto.com/sectors/technology/enpowered-launches-into-energy-saving/|website=StartUp HERE Toronto|accessdate=18 July 2017|date=9 May 2016}}</ref> before moving to the Velocity Incubator at the [[University of Waterloo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Why I made my StartUp Pledge {{!}} StartUp Pledge|url=https://uwaterloo.ca/startup-pledge/why-i-made-my-startup-pledge|website=StartUp Pledge|accessdate=18 July 2017|language=en|date=4 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Eye on electricity rates {{!}} Tomas van Stee, HBA ’13|url=https://www.ivey.uwo.ca/news/in-the-media/2016/7/eye-on-electricity-rates-tomas-van-stee-hba-13/|website=Ivey Business School|accessdate=18 July 2017|language=en}}</ref>

In the summer of 2016, EnPowered began working with consumers in Ontario in an open-beta.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ottawasun.com/2016/05/01/new-business-says-group-buying-will-save-some-homeowners-money-on-hydro-gas-bills|title=New business says group-buying will save some homeowners money on hydro, gas bills|last=|first=|date=|website=Ottawa Sun|publisher=Ottawa Sun|access-date=2016-12-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://velocity.uwaterloo.ca/2016/05/enpowered-launches-into-energy-saving-2/|title=EnPowered launches into energy saving – Velocity|last=|first=|date=May 10, 2016|website=velocity.uwaterloo.ca|publisher=University of Waterloo|access-date=2016-12-20}}</ref>

The company introduced the [[Group buying|group-buying]] system, where customers that use at least 50 percent of their electricity during the day are placed in one group. The group then turns into a larger volume with more customers added, allowing them to pay less.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/business/2016/07/15/group-buying-hydro-startup-hopes-to-cut-bills.html|title=Group-buying hydro startup hopes to cut bills|last=Stevenson|first=Verity|date=July 15, 2016|website=thestar.com|publisher=Toronto Star|access-date=2016-12-20}}</ref>
According to the company, users are mandated to sign up with their local hydro account number.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stevenson|first1=Verity|title=Group-buying hydro startup hopes to cut bills {{!}} OurWindsor.ca|url=https://www.ourwindsor.ca/news-story/6770043-group-buying-hydro-startup-hopes-to-cut-bills/|website=OurWindsor.ca|accessdate=18 July 2017|language=en-CA|date=15 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ottawacitizen.com/news/local-news/new-business-says-group-buying-will-save-some-homeowners-money-on-hydro-gas-bills|title=New business says group-buying will save some homeowners money on hydro, gas bills|last=Butler|first=Don|date=2016-05-02|work=|newspaper=Ottawa Citizen|language=en-US|access-date=2016-12-20|via=}}</ref>

