{{unreferenced|date=December 2012}}
[[File:Solbus Solcity 12 LNG in Kielce 2008.jpg|thumbnail|Solbus Solcity 12 LNG]] [[File:Solbus Solcity 12 LNG rear - engine.jpg|thumbnail|Back side and LNG engine of the bus]]
The '''Solbus Solcity 12 LNG''' is a [[Low-floor bus|fully low-floor]] [[single-decker bus]] manufactured by [[Solbus]] SA in [[Transportation in Poland|Poland]]. The bus is the first to be powered by [[LNG|liquid]] [[natural gas]] in [[Transportation in Europe|Mainland Europe]]. Fueling the bus takes 3–5 minutes.
The first LNG Solcity's were produced in 2010; the model was perfected at the end of 2011. In 2012, the bus was exhibited in the Hannower IAA [[motor show]].
